The uncertainty over the Paris Saint-Germain bench for the 2022/23 season looks to be all but settled. Mauricio Pochettino and his coaching staff have come to an agreement with the club and will now be consigned to the PSG history books. According to L’Equipe, the Argentine an coach, who had failed to reach an agreement regarding the termination of his contract at the Parc des Princes, has accepted a payment of 10 million euros as compensation for the remaining year which was left on his PSG deal.   Calabar Port roars back to life after three years of…     Drogba: Osimhen can be ‘best striker in the…     Tanzania side, Azam unveil Plateau United’s Ndala   As a result, the PSG bench is now vacant but not for long. Christophe Galtier has already confirmed his departure from Nice and will be the next person to take over the position that Pochettino has left in Paris. The 50-year-old won a league title and a French Cup in his year and a half in charge, but was unable to achieve the Champions League success he was tasked with. The Parisians were knocked out by Real Madrid in the second round of the 2021-22 competition after conceding three goals in 17 second half minutes at the Bernabeu in the second leg.